Three people have died while three others have been rushed to the J.M Kariuki Memorial Hospital in critical condition following an accident involving a lorry and saloon car along the Nyahururu-Gigil Highway. The accident occurred on Monday morning at Teachers area, Ol Kalou. Eyewitnesses said the saloon car was headed to Gilgil from Ol Kalou with four occupants while the lorry was headed in the opposite direction. The salon car lost control as it swerved to avoid a pothole and crashed head-on with the oncoming lorry. Photos by Ndichu Wainaina More to follow...